        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:36PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 536 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Carson City, or 10 miles northeast of Ionia,
moving east at 20 mph. A second strong thunderstorm was near Ashley,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Carson City...         Elsie...               Eureka...
North Star...          Maple Rapids...        Ashley...
Perrinton...           Hubbardston...         Bannister...
Palo...                Pompeii...             Middleton...
Butternut...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
